.SH NAME
svc_normal_to_secure_shm_thread \- the function to run in the kthread
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" svc_normal_to_secure_shm_thread
.BI "(void *data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "data" 12
data pointer for kthread function
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Service layer driver creates stratix10_svc_smc_hvc_shm kthread on CPU
node 0, its function stratix10_svc_secure_shm_thread is used to query the
physical address of memory block reserved by secure monitor software at
secure world.

\fBsvc_normal_to_secure_shm_thread\fP calls \fBdo_exit\fP directly since it is a
standlone thread for which no one will call \fBkthread_stop\fP or return when
'\fBkthread_should_stop\fP' is true.
